      <div class="ip-pricing-context">
        <p class="ip-context-paragraph">iPod repair costs depend on the model and parts availability — as a fully discontinued product line, some iPod components are increasingly scarce and can cost more than equivalent smartphone parts. <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-ca/ipod" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="ip-context-link">Apple's iPod support documentation</a> still provides useful reference for troubleshooting before committing to a repair.</p>
        <p class="ip-context-paragraph">Many customers are surprised that repairing an older iPod Classic can cost more than expected due to the hard drive mechanism and limited parts supply. <a href="https://www.ifixit.com/Search?query=ipod+classic+teardown" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="ip-context-link">iFixit's iPod Classic teardown guides</a> explain why the click wheel assembly and hard drive are the most involved repairs on these devices.</p>
        <p class="ip-context-paragraph">If the repair cost doesn't make financial sense for your iPod model, we'll walk you through alternatives — including whether your music library can be recovered and transferred to a modern device, or whether a pre-owned iPod from our inventory might be a better option.</p>
