  <section class="ip-faq-section" id="faqs">
    <div class="ip-container">
      <div class="ip-section-header">
        <h2 class="ip-section-title">iPod Repair FAQs</h2>
        <p class="ip-section-subtitle">Common questions about iPod repair at Mobile Tech Lab in Winnipeg</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ip-faq-list">
        <details class="ip-faq-item">
          <summary class="ip-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you still repair older iPod models in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ip-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ip-faq-answer">Yes — we repair all iPod generations including iPod Classic, Nano, Shuffle, Mini, and all seven generations of iPod Touch. We maintain legacy parts suppliers specifically for discontinued Apple devices, so we can still service models that most repair shops stopped supporting years ago.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ip-faq-item">
          <summary class="ip-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you recover music from a broken iPod in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ip-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ip-faq-answer">In many cases yes — we offer data recovery services for damaged, water-damaged, and non-booting iPods. Recovery success depends on the nature of the failure, and we assess the device before charging anything so you know what's possible before committing.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ip-faq-item">
          <summary class="ip-faq-summary">
            <span>How long does an iPod repair take in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ip-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ip-faq-answer">Most iPod Touch repairs are completed same-day in 1–2 hours at our Winnipeg St. Vital location. iPod Classic, Nano, and Shuffle repairs may take 1–3 business days depending on parts availability for your specific model and generation.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ip-faq-item">
          <summary class="ip-faq-summary">
            <span>Is it worth repairing my old iPod?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ip-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ip-faq-answer">It depends on the model and the repair needed — a battery replacement on an iPod Touch 7th Gen often makes great financial sense, while a screen repair on a 1st Gen iPod Nano may cost more than the device is worth. We always give you an honest assessment before starting any repair so you can make an informed decision.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ip-faq-item">
          <summary class="ip-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair iPod Classic click wheels in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ip-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ip-faq-answer">Yes — we repair and replace click wheel assemblies on iPod Classic and Nano models. Click wheel issues are one of the most common failures on older iPods and parts are still available for most generations, though availability varies — contact us to confirm your model.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ip-faq-item">
          <summary class="ip-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you replace the battery in an iPod Classic?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ip-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ip-faq-answer">Yes — iPod Classic battery replacement is one of our most requested legacy repairs and can dramatically extend the life of your device. We use quality replacement cells and the repair typically takes 1–2 business days depending on parts availability.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ip-faq-item">
          <summary class="ip-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair iPod Touch screens in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ip-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ip-faq-answer">Yes — we replace cracked and unresponsive screens on all seven generations of iPod Touch at our Winnipeg shop. Most iPod Touch screen replacements are completed same-day and carry a warranty depending on the part tier selected.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ip-faq-item">
          <summary class="ip-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you fix an iPod that won't turn on?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ip-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ip-faq-answer">Yes — a non-responsive iPod is often caused by a fully depleted battery, a failed display connection, or a corrupted firmware issue. We run free diagnostics to identify the root cause before recommending any repair.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ip-faq-item">
          <summary class="ip-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you offer a warranty on iPod repairs?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ip-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ip-faq-answer">Yes — screen repairs carry a 30-day to lifetime warranty depending on the part tier. Battery replacements include a 90-day warranty, and most other repairs carry a lifetime warranty on parts and labour — even on legacy iPod models.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ip-faq-item">
          <summary class="ip-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair iPods in Thompson, MB?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ip-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ip-faq-answer">Yes — our Thompson location at 300 Mystery Lake Rd #1530 accepts iPod repairs and walk-ins Monday through Saturday 10AM–6PM. For older or less common iPod models, calling ahead helps us confirm parts availability before your visit.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

